<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,152,642]" pageId="8" pageNumber="40">
All males of this new species were collected in flight near a Brazilian vegetation 
<typeStatus box="[1166,1217,461,487]" pageId="8" pageNumber="40">type</typeStatus>
called Campos de Altitude. The specimens, as other insects, were collected while exhibiting hilltopping behavior at the hilltops in Paraná State. The only female specimen was collected with Malaise trap, an unusual trap for stag beetles. 
<taxonomicName box="[151,315,577,602]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Leptinopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,315,577,602]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="40">Leptinopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are all diurnal and frequently collected at hilltops, feeding at sap flows, or inside nondecayed, dead logs.
</paragraph>
